<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Rosemont</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Rosemont is a developing, family-friendly neighborhood that was built in the year 1958. It is located in the Calgary northwest quadrant, surrounded by 23rd Avenue, 14th Street, Cambrian Drive and Northmount Drive. The community’s population has grown to about 4, 521 residents.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Rosemont real estate comprises large-sized private lots. Nearly all homes have 28 percent open area in the form of spacious yards. The external architecture of homes is further enhanced by gorgeous trees and plantations. Most homes have rear garages as this helps preserve the beauty of the home’s front side. Several homes in the community of Rosemont, particularly those located on Crescent Road, offer spectacular views of the surrounding mountains. The other properties provide views of downtown Okotoks or the famous Sheep River Valley. The Rosemont Community Association or RCA is responsible for meeting the needs of all residents. The average price of a home is $544,900.</p>
        </div>
